cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the properties of deep neural networks, specifically invariance and disentangling, which are important topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper uses information theory to analyze the properties of deep neural networks. The paper also discusses the application of these concepts in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which makes these sub-categories likely as well. Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques to infer the weights of the network, which is a common approach in neural networks (cs.NE).
